SIMPLE: southing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Southing
<hw>South"ing</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Tendency or progress southward; <as>as, the <ex>southing</ex> of
the sun</as>.</def> <rj><au>Emerson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The time at which the moon, or other heavenly body,
passes the meridian of a place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>Distance of any heavenly body
south of the equator; south declination; south latitude.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Surv. & Navigation)</fld> <def>Distance southward
from any point departure or of reckoning, measured on a meridian; --
opposed to <contr>northing</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southly</ent>⟦br⟧
